ShopifyShopify (Legacy)WooCommerceMagentoBigCommerceStandalone <p>In this example, we’re using our quiz ID <code>dbqHqN</code>, which you’ll need to replace for your quiz ID. Here is the code for reference:</p> Example: Basic Slots Template <pre><code>&lt;h3&gt;Hello {{ person|lookup:'Q-dbqHqN ZMiXjj: .Before we get started... what\'s your name?'|default:'' }}!&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here we are making sure the product exists:&lt;/p&gt;
{% if person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_image_url' %}
&lt;p&gt;Cleanser&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt="This is the cleanser image" src="{{ person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_image_url'|default:'' }}" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{{ person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_name'|default:'' }}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{{ person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_price'|default:'' }}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{{ person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_sku'|default:'' }}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="{{ person|lookup:'SLOT-dbqHqN: Step 1: Cleanser - product_0_url'|default:'' }}"&gt;Buy now&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
{% endif %}
{% if person|lookup:'T-dbqHqN: 40s' %}
&lt;p&gt;You are in your forties&lt;/p&gt;
{% endif %}
</code></pre> <p>This example demonstrated that you can not only include custom properties that are passed from the quiz to your Klaviyo account, but you can also use <code>IF-ELSE</code> conditional statements to show/hide content based on the customer’s responses to the quiz.</p> <p>Note: Counting Products</p> <p>Note that when looping through the products, the count starts in 0 (zero), so for example, if you were to display the name of 3 products in a slot you’d have to do it like this:</p> <pre><code>```html
