"tags": ["30s", "dry_skin"]
</code></pre> Example Answer Structure <p>Each question block in the quiz is represented in the <code>answersByBlock</code> object, including the question type, value, and choices selected.</p> <pre><code>"answersByBlock": {
"qbi-6c4248f5": {
    "type": "first_name",
    "value": "Loretta"
},
"qbc-e8cf3180": {
    "type": "multiple_choice",
    "value": [
    "Fine lines and wrinkles",
    "Hyperpigmentation and discoloration",
    "Enlarged pores"
    ]
}
}
</code></pre> Example Tags <p>Tags are automatically generated based on quiz logic or answers:</p> <pre><code>"tags": ["30s", "dry_skin"]
</code></pre> <p>You can use them to segment leads or filter automations in Zapier.</p> Product Recommendations <p>If your quiz includes product recommendation logic, these are sent in the recommendationsBySlot field, grouped by result sections or slots:</p> <pre><code>"recommendationsBySlot": {
"rsbs-520511f2": [
    "gid://shopify/Product/9634315436325",
    "gid://shopify/Product/9634314584357"
]
}
</code></pre> Result Page Content <p>The quiz’s result page content is included in two sections:</p> <p><code>resultSections</code> → Organized view of all result blocks (headings, text, products, etc.)</p> <p><code>resultContentByBlock</code>→ Flattened key-value pairs for each block reference</p> <p>Example:</p> <pre><code>"recommendationsBySlot": {
"rsbs-520511f2": [
    "gid://shopify/Product/9634315436325",
    "gid://shopify/Product/9634314584357"
]
}
</code></pre> <p>During the setup, you can check the quiz data that Zapier will receive from the quiz. This includes:</p> <ul> <li>Email addresses of quiz participants.</li> <li>Recommended products.</li> <li>Responses to quiz questions.</li> </ul> <p></p> <p>After configuring the triggers, you can test the connection in Zapier's <code>Test trigger</code> section to ensure the correct data is being captured.</p> <p></p> <p>During the setup, you can check the quiz data that Zapier will receive from the quiz. This includes:</p> <ul> <li>Email addresses of quiz participants.</li> <li>Recommended products.</li> <li>Responses to quiz questions.</li> </ul> <p></p> <p>After configuring the triggers, you can test the connection in Zapier's <code>Test trigger</code> section to ensure the correct data is being captured.</p> <p></p> <p>During the setup, you can check the quiz data that Zapier will receive from the quiz. This includes:</p> <ul> <li>Email addresses of quiz participants.</li> <li>Recommended products.</li> <li>Responses to quiz questions.</li> </ul> <p></p> <p>After configuring the triggers, you can test the connection in Zapier's <code>Test trigger</code> section to ensure the correct data is being captured.</p> <p></p> <p>During the setup, you can check the quiz data that Zapier will receive from the quiz. This includes:</p> <ul> <li>Email addresses of quiz participants.</li> <li>Recommended products.</li> <li>Responses to quiz questions.</li> </ul> <p></p> <p>After configuring the triggers, you can test the connection in Zapier's <code>Test trigger</code> section to ensure the correct data is being captured.</p> <p></p> <p>During the setup, you can check the quiz data that Zapier will receive from the quiz. This includes:</p> <ul> <li>Email addresses of quiz participants.</li> <li>Recommended products.</li> <li>Responses to quiz questions.</li> </ul> <p></p> <p>After configuring the triggers, you can test the connection in Zapier's <code>Test trigger</code> se